<subSubSection box="[199,1394,577,602]" pageId="9" pageNumber="504" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,505,926]" box="[199,1394,577,602]" pageId="9" pageNumber="504">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,562,577,602]" pageId="9" pageNumber="504">Habitat (as in Indian records).</emphasis>
Marine, intertidal; medium sand, 
<quantity box="[943,1012,577,601]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="504" unit="cm" value="20.0">20 cm</quantity>
below surface at mid-water level.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="504" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,505,926]" pageId="9" pageNumber="504">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,613,638]" pageId="9" pageNumber="504">Distribution.</emphasis>
Originally found in the bay of Naples (
<collectingCountry box="[807,863,613,638]" name="Italy" pageId="9" pageNumber="504">Italy</collectingCountry>
), the species has subsequently been reported from several areas and localities including the Mediterranean Sea, North Europe, British islands, Atlantic coast of the 
<collectingCountry box="[151,207,686,710]" name="United States of America" pageId="9" pageNumber="504">USA</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[261,322,685,710]" name="India" pageId="9" pageNumber="504">India</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Naidu, K. V. &amp; Rao, G. C." box="[332,562,685,710]" pageId="9" pageNumber="504" pagination="169" refId="ref9261" refString="Naidu, K. V. &amp; Rao, G. C. (2004) Gastrotricha. In: Fauna of India and the adjacent countries. Zoological Survey of India, Kolkata, pp. 169." type="book chapter" year="2004">Naidu &amp; Rao (2004)</bibRefCitation>
indicated the species to be present also in 
<collectingCountry box="[1035,1178,685,710]" name="South Korea" pageId="9" pageNumber="504">South Korea</collectingCountry>
, however we could not find evidence in this regard, and the species is not included among the invertebrate fauna of 
<collectingCountry box="[1184,1252,722,745]" name="South Korea" pageId="9" pageNumber="504">Korea</collectingCountry>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Lee, J." box="[1312,1422,722,746]" pageId="9" pageNumber="504" pagination="1 - 85" refId="ref9031" refString="Lee, J. (2012) Invertebrate fauna of Korea. Fol. 11. No. 1. Marine gastrotrichs (Gastrotricha). National Institute of Biological Resources, Sang Pal Lee, Incheon, pp. 1 - 85." type="book chapter" year="2012">Lee 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="504" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,505,926]" pageId="9" pageNumber="504">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,757,782]" pageId="9" pageNumber="504">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Todaro, M. A. &amp; Hummon, W. D. &amp; Balsamo, M. &amp; Fregni, E. &amp; Tongiorgi, P." box="[327,565,757,782]" pageId="9" pageNumber="504" pagination="75 - 137" refId="ref10902" refString="Todaro, M. A., Hummon, W. D., Balsamo, M., Fregni, E. &amp; Tongiorgi, P. (2001) Inventario dei Gastrotrichi marini italiani: una checklist annotata. Atti Societa Toscana di Scienze Naturali Memorie, Serie B, 107, 75 - 137." type="journal article" year="2001">
Todaro 
<emphasis box="[418,472,757,782]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="504">et al</emphasis>
. (2001)
</bibRefCitation>
changed the species name ending from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Remane" authorityYear="1927" box="[1050,1209,758,781]" class="Gastrotricha (awaiting allocation)" family="Thaumastodermatidae" genus="Echinodasys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Macrodasyida" pageId="9" pageNumber="504" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="species" species="megastoma">
<emphasis box="[1050,1209,758,781]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="504">T. megastoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Remane" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[1256,1436,758,781]" class="Gastrotricha (awaiting allocation)" family="Thaumastodermatidae" genus="Tetranchyroderma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Macrodasyida" pageId="9" pageNumber="504" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="species" species="megastomum">
<emphasis box="[1256,1436,758,781]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="504">T. megastomum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
according to the genus gender. According to the literature, the species appears to be eurytopic, having been found at different depths and in sediments of various grain size. The wide distribution, the variety of habitats and descriptions, some of which are discordant, call for a better comparison of the geographic populations, hopefully based also on molecular data.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
